"{\"uid\": \"thegatewaypundit.com-2024-08-us-most-successful-country-olympic-history-lets-kept\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Olympics have always been a crucial component of nationalism, patriotism, and soft power on the global stage, first with the US competing against the USSR and now with the US competing against China and Russia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 154, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9988031149798395, \"rank\": 0.0011888722611334878, \"text\": \"USSR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 176, \"end\": 178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 207, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902798511187141, \"rank\": 0.007077252066682068, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US Olympic success stems from hard work, fair selection, the world's best feeder system, and an American spirit of patriotism and perseverance.\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 215, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999972718834139, \"rank\": 2.7278480837051956e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US should not allow athletes to disrespect the flag, and DEI should not play any role in selecting athletes, including at the high school and university levels.\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, the emasculation of boys, the increased prevalence of online activities, the lack of support for youth sports, and the widespread use of pharmaceutical drugs to decrease testosterone and energy levels in children are weakening the nation.\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Up until now, the US has been the best, and we should strive to keep it that way.\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every four years, China claims they will beat the US in the Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 909, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they have only won the goldmedal count once, in 2008, in Beijing, where they could capitalize on the built-in advantages granted to the hosting country,and also cheat.\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 1112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999916881279, \"rank\": 8.311975507180794e-09, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States is themost successful countryin Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.99999293226798, \"rank\": 4.9375195351044315e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As of the end of the 2021 Tokyo Olympics, approximately 5,325 gold medals and 16,725 total medals have been awarded in all Summer Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States has won 1,174 gold medals and a total of 2,980 medals, making it the most successful country in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.99999293226798, \"rank\": 4.9375195351044315e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the first modern Olympics in 1896 until World War II, the US won the gold medal count in all but three Olympiads: 1900, which was won by France; 1908 by the UK; and 1936 by Germany.\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 160