, \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, the US has won all but one, with the US winning five times and China just once, in 2008.\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2235, \"end\": 2240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the first days of each Olympiad, the US usually lags in the gold medal count, coming in as low as fifth or sixth.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2301, \"end\": 2303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is because of the schedule ofswimming and running events.\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the swimming events increase towards days three and four of the Olympiad, the US medal count rises.\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Currently, the US is two golds behind China, with several days of swimming and a host of running events yet to come.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2559, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2582, \"end\": 2587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An odd anomaly about the US is the frequency with which it wins the total medal count.\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Currently, the US has 50% more total medals than China, while China leads in gold.\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2764, \"end\": 2766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2798, \"end\": 2803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Detractors often claim that the US only wins because of its larger population.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2865, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, if that were the case, medal counts would align with population size, meaning India and China would earn more than the US, followed by Indonesia, Pakistan, and Nigeria.\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\"