national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3128, \"end\": 3133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, Bangladesh, which has never won an Olympic gold medal, has a larger population than Russia, a gold medal powerhouse.\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3245, \"end\": 3255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh\", \"score\": 0.9978987418210427, \"rank\": 0.00197433965737796, \"text\": \"Bangladesh\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh\"}, {\"begin\": 3329, \"end\": 3335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902798511187141, \"rank\": 0.007077252066682068, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This discrepancy highlights that factors beyond population size, such as investment in sports infrastructure, training programs, and a culture that promotes athletic excellence, play a crucial role in Olympic success.\", \"from\": 3362, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The US has athletes who receive superior training.\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3585, \"end\": 3587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No matter where you are born in the world, if you wanted to be an Olympic swimmer or runner, you would choose the USA for your training over Bangladesh or Indonesia.\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3746, \"end\": 3749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8052240485106718, \"rank\": 0.24189026477157788, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3773, \"end\": 3783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh\", \"score\": 0.9978987418210427, \"rank\": 0.00197433965737796, \"text\": \"Bangladesh\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, even for sports where the US is not always the winner, with few exceptions such as table tennis, you would still choose training in the US over most other countries.\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3833, \"end\": 3835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3943, \"end\": 3945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The superior infrastructure, experienced coaches, and comprehensive support systems in the US make it a preferred destination for aspiring Olympians globally.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 4131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4064, \"end\": 4066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another strength, of the US, is the selection process.\", \"from\": 4133, \"to\": 4187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4158, \"end\": 4160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the United States, a significant number of children participate in scholastic and collegiate sports.\", \"from\": 4188, \"to\": 4291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4195, \"end\": 4208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.99999293226798, \"rank\": 4.9375195351044315e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US is essentially the only nation that has a widespread system of scholastic and collegiate sports feeding into the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4292, \"to\": 4421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4296, \"end\": 4298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to recent data, approximately53.8% of childrenaged 6 to 17, which equates to about 26.8 million kids, played on a sports team or took sports lessons in 2022.\", \"from\": 4422, \"to\": 4589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the collegiate level, the NCAA reports that there are roughly 480,000 student-athletes competing across various sports.\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4619, \"end\": 4623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9965628374178539, \"rank\": 0.0034490168564180242, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US wrestlerJordan Burroughsserves as a prime example of how stringent U.S. competition is and how difficult it can be to make the Olympic team.\", \"from\": 4714, \"to\": 4857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4714, \"end\": 4716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jordan Burroughs is considered the most successful wrestler still competing, with a remarkable record that includes an Olympic gold medal (2012), World Championship gold medals in 2017 and 2021, bronze medals in 2018 and 2019, Pan American Championship gold medals from 2020 to 2023, and World Cup gold medals in 2018 and 2019.\", \"from\": 4858, \"to\": 5185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4858, \"end\": 4874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Burroughs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Burroughs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Burroughs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Burroughs\"}, {\"begin\": 5085, \"end\": 5110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999838999647221, \"rank\": 1.555724452536192e-05, \"text\": \"Pan American Championship\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Wrestling_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet, he still had to compete for a spot on the 2024 Olympics and failed to make the team.\", \"from\": 5186, \"to\": 5279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly, the Olympics isanother areawhere the US may fail if the liberalshave their way.\", \"from\": 5281, \"to\": 5367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5325, \"end\": 5327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Allowing men to compete in women's sports or selecting athletes based on diversity, rather than analytics, will hamstring the US's ability to continue to dominate.\", \"from\": 5368, \"to\": 5531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5494, \"end\": 5496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Allowing our athletes to kneel rather than salute the flag, turning the Olympics into a wokepropaganda tool, will destroy the spirit of the games and allow countries like China and Russia to surpass the US.\", \"from\": 5532, \"to\": 5738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5703, \"end\": 5708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999996703684677, \"rank\": 2.144950811455994e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 5713, \"end\": 5719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902798511187141, \"rank\": 0.007077252066682068, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5735, \"end\": 5737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996636329909, \"rank\": 3.363616873739827e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You canemail Antonio Graceffo here, andread more of Antonio Graceffo's articles here.\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5755, \"end\": 5762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonio_Dawson\", \"score\":